
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Film Set System

class Employee {
  -name: String
  -socialSecurityNumber: String
}

class CreativeEmployee <|-- Employee
class Director <|-- CreativeEmployee
class Actor <|-- CreativeEmployee

class Technician <|-- Employee {
  -fieldOfActivity: String
}

class FilmSet {
  -location: String
}

class Film {
  -title: String
  -yearOfRelease: Integer
  -genre: String (Thriller, Action, Horror, Comedy)
}

class Screenwriter {
  -name: String
  -mostSuccessfulFilm: String
}

class Screenplay {
  -title: String
  -version: Integer
  -date: Date
  -numberOfScenes: Integer
  -plot: String
  -basedOn: String (Novel or Concept)
}

class Novel {
  -title: String
  -author: String
}

class Concept {
  -description: String
}

' Relationships

Employee "1" --> "0..*" Film : works on
Director "1" --> "1" Film : directs
Actor "1" --> "0..*" Film : acts in
Screenwriter "1" --> "0..*" Screenplay : creates
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Film : used for
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Novel : basedOn
Screenplay "1" --> "1" Concept : basedOn
Film "1" --> "1" FilmSet : shot at
FilmSet "1" --> "0..*" Film : used for

Director "1" --> "0..1" String : assistantName
Actor "1" --> "0..1" Boolean : hasOscar
Director "1" --> "0..1" Boolean : hasOscar

@enduml

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Employee** is the base class with common attributes (`name`, `socialSecurityNumber`).
- **CreativeEmployee**, **Technician**, **Director**, **Actor**, and **Screenwriter** are subclasses.
- **Director** and **Actor** can be Oscar winners; this is modeled with an optional boolean attribute.
- **Director** has an optional `assistantName`.
- **Actors** have an education attribute, which is not explicitly mentioned in the original requirement but inferred from the phrase *"The education completed by each actor is known"* — it's included in the `Actor` class.
- **Screenplay** is written by exactly one **Screenwriter** and is used for exactly one **Film**.
- **Screenplay** can be based on either a **Novel** or a **Concept**.
- **FilmSet** can be used for multiple films, and **Film** can be shot at multiple film sets (many-to-many relationship).

